Intuition:
Following the approach given in the problem statement.

Approach:
1. Finding max element for each index and storing it in mx[].
2. Storing the gcd of nums[i] and mx[i] in prefix[].
3. Sort the prefix[].
4. Using two pointers, p1 and p2, where p1 points to the starting index of the array and p2 points to the end of the array.
5. p1 should travel only till the mid of the array.
6. Find gcd of the smallest and largest elements in the prefix array and add them.
7. Return the sum.

Complexity:
Time complexity: O(nlogn)
Space complexity: O(n)
